title.narrative: 503 EDUCATION FOR OUT OF SCHOOL GIRLS AND BOYS

description.narrative: Government and partners have increased capacity to deliver gender responsive and equitable, flexible, inclusive quality elementary education for out of school girls and boys,which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: Government and partners have increased capacity to deliver gender responsive and equitable, flexible, inclusive quality elementary education for out of school girls and boys

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, 540,000 out-of-school children (287,000 boys and 253,000 girls) have been enrolled in schools and special training (accelerated learning) programmes in states with a higher burden of out-of-school children. Capacity has been strengthened in states on special training (accelerated learning). Flexible learning programmes have been identified through a call for solutions and showcased at the national level, to be further included in a database of solutions as part of GenU India/YuWaah, for access by states and partners to take forward. Innovative flexible learning strategies are also being demonstrated with UNICEF support in states. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
